## Steps to Reproduce

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Status | Comments | Environment |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Enter the main page at https://hospitapp.vercel.app/ | The home page should render with a "Buscar" button in the middle of the page. | Passed | None | Mac (Server) - Client (Google Chrome) |
| 2 | Click on the "Buscar" Button | The application should redirect to a page where filter fields can be selected and IPSs can be watched. | Passed | None | Mac (Server) - Client (Google Chrome) |
| 3 | Select the "EPS" options (1 or many) you want to filter IPSs with, "Specialties" options (1 or many) you want to filter IPSs with, and the "distance" option (just 1) for the range of search. | The search button should display the IPSs that match the selected options, unless the location permission hasn't been accepted or rejected, which will disable the search button. | Passed | None | Mac (Server) - Client (Google Chrome) |
| 4 | Click on the "Buscar" button | The system should show the IPSs that match the specified filters and location. | Passed | None | Mac (Server) - Client (Google Chrome) |
| 5 | Accept the location permission request if you want to use the location feature. If not, do not accept it. | The system should show the IPSs that matched the specified filters and location. | Passed | None | Mac (Server) - Client (Google Chrome) |

